The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | Good Morning
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                       Good Morning
      Hello It's Friday , July 18 , 2008                      
	Book launch    Launch of Seeing is Believing, selected writings on cinema by Chidananda Das Gupta followed by a discussion on How Indian is Indian Cinema? at Crossword Bookstore, Elgin Road, 6.30pm.     
	School    Vidyarthee Vrata, freshers welcome at Ramakrishna MIssion Centenary Primary School, Gopal Lala Tagore Road, 7am.    
	Store    Opening of a new store of Ananda Publishers at C-9 Bagha Jatin Colony, 4pm.    
	Art watch    Preview of Colourscapes II, an exhibition by Sukanta Das at Kanvas Art Gallery, 6pm.  Swaroop Mukherjis paintings on the Ganpathi festival in Mumbai at The Art Gallery, ITC Sonar, 7pm.  Kolkata Smiles 08, an exhibition of cartoons, at Weavers Studio Centre for the Arts, 11am.				 																																	   Art Mela, an exhibition of art works at Gallery Exposure, 3pm-8pm.				 																																	   An exhibition of paintings and sculptures at Mon Art Gallerie, 11am to 7pm.   
